    "body": "Wow, that \"you touched it last\" spiel never fails to bring on a spontaneous attack of joy... :)\n\nYes, yes I did. having uniform image size improves the overall appearance of\nthe docs. As for blurriness, I looked (very closely) and I guess you're right. but\nhonestly, it seems like a minor issue to me.\n\nThe reason I conformed everything to 6,4 was specifically because previously\ndifferent figures were forced to differing dimensions.\n\nJust dropping the spec does not work, have a look at the figure just above\nhttp://jorisvandenbossche.github.io/example-pandas-docs/html-plot-withoutwidth/visualization.html#box-plotting\n\nThere was a similar issues opened in the past, though I can never find anything with GH search,\nwhich suggested a workaround that never worked for me.\n\nIf you can find a way to sharpen the images and keep the dimensions uniform,\nthat's great, otherwise I'm for leaving things as is until such a solution does turn up.\n"
  },
